Chapter  4 

Attitudes  Towards  Risk 

In  the  previous  lecture,  we  explored  the  implications  of  expected  utility maximization. 
In  this  lecture,  considering  the  lotteries  over  money,  I  will  introduce  the  basic  notions 
regarding  risk,  such  as  risk  aversion  and  certainty  equivalence.  Understanding  these 
concepts  is  essential  to  follow most  areas  in modern  economics. 

